<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">February</hi> 8, 1895.—Read, referred
                            to the Committee on Foreign Relations, and ordered to be printed.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="italic">To the Senate and House of
                                Representatives.</hi></p>
                        <p>I transmit herewith for the information of the Congress a copy of a
                            telegraphic dispatch just received from Mr. Willis, our minister to
                            Hawaii, with a copy of the reply thereto which was immediately sent by
                            the Secretary of State.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grover Cleveland.</hi></signed>
                            <lb/>
                            <dateline rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Mansion</hi>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-08"><hi rend="italic">February 8, 1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>